# Step 29.y reconciliation: widen diagnostic-artifact ignores. These
# patterns capture the second wave of operator scratch surfaces that
# escaped the C33 pass — chat-session transcripts, dated evidence and
# probe dumps, and cross-step snapshot logs. Canonical record of any
# incident lives in CloudWatch + admin_audit_logs + DRIFTS.md; the
# files matched here are per-session intermediates and forensics that
# should never be committed.
*.transcript.txt
*-transcript-*.txt
*-evidence-*.json
*-evidence-*.log
*-probe-*.json
*-probe-*.log
*-snapshot-*.log

# Step 30a.2-3 reconciliation: third wave of operator scratch. The T9
# closure leg, the post-checkout cookie debugging spree, the SES policy
# fix cycle, and the Amplify custom-rules tuning all left per-session
# JSON / PS1 / py shrapnel at repo root. None of these are referenced
# from any committed script; canonical record lives in DRIFTS.md and
# CloudWatch. Patterns below are surgical -- they intentionally do NOT
# catch alembic migrations, app/ code, scripts/deploy_*.{sh,ps1}, or
# scripts/td-backend-snapshot-*.json (if we ever need a tracked example).

# T9 (GATE 5 closure) operator scratch -- PS1 probes, py probes, etc.
t9_*.ps1
t9_*.py

# Ad-hoc task-def JSON dumps (deploy scripts write to $env:TEMP, not
# repo root, so anything matching these at repo root is sediment).
backend-[0-9]*.json
backend-td-*.json
worker-td-*.json
td[0-9]*.json
td-backend-rev*.json
scripts/td-backend-rev*.json
scripts/td-backend-*-snapshot.json

# SES policy fix cycle (pre-Step 30a.2 email-delivery hardening).
luciel_ses_policy*.json
ses_send_policy.json

# Amplify custom-rules + envvars patch sediment.
amplify_*.json

# One-off operator scripts that were never meant to be tracked.
add_beat.py
prod_safety_check.py
register_r2.py

